# UI Components

When adding new UI components, always use shadcn/ui components.

## Installing shadcn Components

To add a new shadcn component, use:

```bash
bunx --bun shadcn@latest add <component-name>
```

Note: This project uses Bun as the package manager. Always use `bunx --bun` for running shadcn CLI.

## Available Components

Check available components at: https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components

## Component Guidelines

- Always import shadcn components from `@/components/ui/*`
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling (already configured)
- Follow the existing component patterns in the codebase
- Prefer composition over custom implementations

## Examples

```typescript
// Good - using shadcn
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
import { DropdownMenu } from "@/components/ui/dropdown-menu"

// Bad - custom implementation when shadcn exists
import CustomButton from "./custom-button"
```
